FUNCTION DESCRIPTION:
This speci?cation describes the implementation of global company requirement "Konzerncodierung im Mo-
torsteuerger�t". The implementation will not support any former variant coding strategies.
Special functionalities are activatable or deactivatable inside ECU via variant coding. Therefore NC_VAR_CODE
bytes (named blocks) of coding data will be used, which can be send/read via service tool. Additionally there
are 4 bytes of calibration data used for special variant coding purposes.
Coding cell number handling for calibration:
The variant coding works internal with logical enumeration of the coding cells and coding blocks. Therefore
the ?rst coding cell is cell number 0 and the ?rst coding block is block 0.
The enumaration of the coding cells and blocks in this speci?cation starts with 1 (technical enumeration) and
also the display names of the attribut bytes and coding blocks are starting with 1 as ?rst value.
Due to technical reasons, the application of coding cells in the following tables has to be done with the logical
enumeration (starting with 0):

68.2.1.1 Description of ACTION_SYCF_ChkVarCodCdn (OUT <CDN_OK>)
This Action is de?ned only if NC_NR_VERS_VAR_COD >= 0x420.
Following conditions will be checked at variant coding:
IF ( LV_IGK = 1 AND LV_ES = 1 )
#IF NC_STATE_STST_CONF == ACTIVE
#THEN AND LV_STST_STOP_CYC() = 0
#ENDIF
THEN
IF (ACTION_FARM_GetPermission(NC_FID_VAR_COD_GEAR_PSN_VLD)
THEN IF (STATE_GLV_ETCU = 0 "NEUT" OR STATE_GLV_ETCU = 1 "PRKG")
THEN CDN_OK = 1
ELSE CDN_OK = 0
ELSE CDN_OK = 1
ELSE CDN_OK = 0
Application Hints: NC_FID_VAR_COD_GEAR_PSN_VLD is used to check the gear position, if STATE_GLV_ETCU
has been delivered by a valid signal. If e.g. STATE_GLV_ETCU is deiliverd by TCU_11, a link pattern as showed
below (farm editor) is used, to check the gear position.
Usually projects with MLBevo or MQB use TCU11, whereas MLB projects use CTU03 and PQX projects use
TCU01.

There is a dependency between RSC and LONG_VAR channel as they save both the variant coding redun-
dantly. A counter of written instances (VAR_COD_CTR) will be saved at each saving within the instance.
1. At update, the ?rst of 2 instances seting write request compares its own counter with the counter of sec-
ond instance. The largest counter will be incremend and written as own counter. The second instance
trying to update overtakes the other counter as its own and updates it to NVMY.
In this way it will be ensured the counters are always synchronous and in rising order saved due to the
time of update.
2. After ful?lling the write request the callback function of corresponding instance will be called. Within this
function the second instance will be requested to be written too, in order to ensure the instances to be
from the same time.

to "Bitkipper") the ECU tries to correct this failure by itself using the second channel. If a correction is not
possible, the default coding actions will be done.

68.2.1.5 Default coding
Default coding is a proper basic variant code to be used, if no reliable data is available to be applied and is
given by C_VAR_CODE_DEF[ ].
VAR_COD_DEF is set to C_VAR_CODE_DEF[ ] unless
Default code will be used by failure at reading NVMY. Also, a new delivered ECU causes a default coding.
Following actions will be taken in this case:
- set error memory entry for VAR_COD_DFT instance
- set LV_VAR_COD_DFT to 1
- use default coding calibrated via C_VAR_CODE_DEF [NC_VAR_CODE ]
- tester output: VAG_LONG_VAR_CODE[ ] = 00 00 .. 00 h
If an IMMO download has been executed, the extended default code will be used. This will be indicated by
LV_STATE_VAR_COD_INH_BIT_3_DI = 1.
Besides for the cells with set attribute bit 6 all cells are set to zero by extended default code. The irreversible
once-only codeable cells will maintain the old value, before IMMO download.
The used default code is always indicated by VAR_COD_DEF[NC_VAR_CODE].
Default code will be accepted and applied without any further checks.
68.2.2 Check content of variant code
There are some checks to approve a variant code either from NVMY or arrived from tester.
If tests are approved, the variant code will be used to initialise the corresponding data, otherwise the coding
will be rejected and the current variant code will still be used.
68.2.2.1 Check cell attributes
Variant code is composed of NC_VAR_CODE bytes. Each block frames several cells. Each coding cell consists
of one or more successive bits of a block. Then number of all cells is given by NC_VAR_CODE_CL.
An attribute byte and a coding matrix with a lenght of 8 byte is available for each coding cell. Each coding
cell will be checked separately.
The coding matrix ID_CODE_MATRIX [NC_VAR_CODE] contains for each coding cell up to 8 accepted values.
Other values will be rejected.
The attribute byte C_ATTR_BYTE [NC_VAR_CODE_CL] de?nes for each coding cell, if and under which condi-
tions, it can be changed.
Following values can be applied for attribute bytes:

Bit 2 (0x02): only values applied in coding matrix are allowed. Not used values of coding matrix has to be

Bit 3 (0x04): the coding cell can be coded only once, i.e. the coding cells with this attribute have to be the
same in the ECU and from the tester, to accept the new code.
In a new delivered ECU LV_STATE_VAR_COD_INH_BIT_3_DI is set to 1 and after ?rst variant coding to 0.

If reversible variant coding is active (LC_CAL_VAR_ATTR_RV = 1), LV_STATE_VAR_COD_INH_BIT_3_DI can be set

This attribute is only applied, if ECU is a production ECU (HW index starts with H) OR if tuning protection

Bit 4 (0x08): a special security level on service tool side is needed to change the content of coding cell.
Bit 5 (0x10): the related coding cell is not allowed to be changed.

resentd by LV_STATE_VAR_COD_INH_BIT_6_DI, could not be set to 1 by any services. It is set to 1 in a new

68.2.2.2 Check cell interdependency
The table ID_NR_MASK_VAR_COD can be used to characterize an interdependency among variants to be
coded.
This table contains 8 rows (0..7) and 8 columns (0..7).
A row consists of 8 cells or 4 cell couples. The even cell of a couple, 0, 2, 4 or 6, contains a coding cell number.
These calibration cells are using the logical numbers (starting with 0) of the coding cells (see also chapter
"Coding cell number handling for calibration") The following cell contains the crucial content of this coding
cell. For example: ID_NR_MASK_VAR_COD[m][3] contains the variant to be coded into the coding cell with the
number entered in ID_NR_MASK_VAR_COD[m][2].
The default value of the table is 0xFF. The table has to be calibrated continuousely, i.e. the value 0xFF at the
begin of a row assigns the end of search in the table. A 0xFF in an applicated row means, that the remaining
cells of this row will not be considered.
The table below containes three rows as example. The third one should only ease the formlized description of
the table.
Idx 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 
0 2 1 35 4 35 5 0xFF 0xFF 
1 3 1 27 2 23 1 0xFF 0xFF 
2 X VARX L VARL M VARM N VARN 
3 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 
4 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 
5 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 
6 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 
7 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 
 
Figure 68.2.2: Example for content of ID_NR_MASK_VAR_COD
The third row restricts the coding of cell number X with the content VARX. To allow this the next 3 cell couples
of the same row are checked:
Cell number L has to be coded with VARL, Cell number M with VARM and Cell number N with VARN, if L, M
and N are distinct numbers.
Are two numbers equal e.g. M = N and VRN != VARM, the cell number M (=N) can consequently be coded
either with variant VARM or VARN.
Example: the table above characterize also the following interdependencies:
- If the STATE_VAR_MKT (cell 2) ist set to 1 (America), the emission STATE_VAR_EMI (cell 35) has to be 4 or 5
(EU6 to GREEN_TAX).
- If the the transmission is manuell (cell 3 is set 1), ACC has to be activated (cell 27 set to 2) and cell 24
(front/quattro) has to be set to 1 (quattro).
Applikation conditions:
IF coding cell [m][0] = 0xFF with m = 0.. 4
THEN end the computation
IF coding cell [m][0] >= NC_VAR_CODE_CL with m = 0 .. 4
(e.g. coding cell [m][n] = 0xF0)
THEN disgard the cell dependency check for this row
IF coding cell [m][n] >= NC_VAR_CODE_CL with m = 0 .. 4 and n = 2, 4 or 6
(e.g. coding cell [m][n] = 0xF0)

68.2.4.3 Further con?guration
68.2.4.3.1 Con?guration of cooling fan:
For Con?guration of cooling fans the following variables needs to be calculated:
STATE_ECFPWM_1 = ID_STATE_ECFPWM [0] [STATE_VAR_ECF]
STATE_ECFPWM_2 = ID_STATE_ECFPWM [1] [STATE_VAR_ECF]
STATE_ECF_3 = ID_STATE_ECF [STATE_VAR_ECF]
STATE_ECF_POW_x = ID_STATE_ECF_POW [x] [STATE_VAR_ECF]
68.2.4.3.2 Con?guration variables depending on drivetrain variant:
Con?guration of active engine and transmission mounts depends on used drivetrain:
IF LV_AT = 1
THEN IF LV_CVT = 0
THEN IF LV_DCT = 0
THEN TRANS_TYP = AT (0H)
ELSE TRANS_TYP = DCT (4H)
ELSE TRANS_TYP = CVT (1H)
ELSE IF LV_VAR_4WD = 0
THEN TRANS_TYP = MT (2H)
ELSE TRANS_TYP = MT_4WD (3H)
END IF
LV_VAR_AEB = ID_VAR_AEB(f(TRANS_TYP))
LV_VAR_ATB = ID_VAR_ATB(f(TRANS_TYP))
68.2.4.3.3 Application requirements:
For runtime reasons valid values should be applied at the beginning of coding matrix ID_CODE_MATRIX. Not
used elements of coding matrix must be calibrated with FFh.

68.2.7.1 Description of ACTION_SYCF_RstVarCod( )
ACTION_SYCF_RstVarCod  ( ) 
This action performs setting of LV_STATE_VAR_COD_INH_BIT_3_DI to active 
 
This action reverse the prevention ?ag of one time codeable variants. It is used only by reversible variant
coding, i.e. LC_CAL_VAR_ATTR_RV = 1.
This functionality is only available if ECU is a production ECU (HW index starts with H) OR if tuning protection
is installed and active (ACTION_SWMD_IsProductionMode returns a 1). If ECU is in sample mode, every variant
can be coded.
This Action has to be called at the end of an IMMO Download and performs following actions:
IF LC_CAL_VAR_ATTR_RV = 1
THEN Set LV_STATE_VAR_COD_INH_BIT_3_DI = 1 and save in NVMY
Set LV_VAR_COD_DFT = 1
STATE_VAR_COD_NVMY = DFT_DNL
- Set error memory entry for VAR_COD_DFT instance,
? Set each cell of code word VAR_CODE[ ] to zero, if in the corresponding attribute byte bit 6 is not set
(C_ATTR_BYTE [cell number] != 0x20).
? Set tester output: LONG_VAR_CODE[ ] = 00 00 .. 00 h, if no code cell has attribute bit 6 set, otherwise
only those cells keep the already coded content.
- Save all changed data to NVMY and wait for successful storage.
A new variant coding will be rejected with NRC 0x22, if the storage has not been completed yet.

SYCF, Variant coding
Engine Code Letters(ECL) are 4 ASCII letters (NC_NR_IDX_ENG_COD).
The assignment has to be done after variant coding. To select the correct ECL, there are two tables:
� ID_IDX_VAR_BLOCK_ENG_COD
This map contains 8 (NC_NR_ENG_COD_VAR) rows with 8 (NC_NR_IDX_TXT_ENG_COD) columns. Every row
corresponds to one possible ECL. The column contains all pairs of variant coding blocks and corresponding
values related to the ECL. Each coding block is de?ned by 2 bytes: The ?rst byte contains the cell number
(using the logical numbers (starting with 0) of the coding cells (see also chapter"Coding cell number handling
for calibration")) and the second byte contains the value of this cell. Not used blocks are ?lled with 0xFFFF.
Every coding cell is checked. If all of this pairs are valid, the row number de?nes the number of the ECL.
� ID_TXT_ENG_COD
If a row with all con?gured coding cells valid is found in ID_IDX_VAR_BLOCK_ENG_COD, this row number de?nes
the column number of ID_TXT_ENG_COD with the corresponding ECL.
� C_TXT_DEF_ENG_COD
If there was NO valid coding cell number / value combination found in ID_IDX_VAR_BLOCK_ENG_COD, the ECL
de?ned in C_TXT_DEF_ENG_COD is used.
Engine Code Letter can Change depending on used variant code as following:
� Calibration Hints:
? 0x0901 means that this cell of ID_IDX_VAR_BLOCK_ENG_COD is valid if coding cell 9 contains the value 1
? 0x1302 means that this cell of ID_IDX_VAR_BLOCK_ENG_COD is valid if coding cell 19(13hex!!) contains
the value 2
? 0xFE01 means that this cell of ID_IDX_VAR_BLOCK_ENG_COD is valid if power class with index 1 is active
? Unused Map cells of ID_IDX_VAR_BLOCK_ENG_COD has to be ?lled with 0xFFFF
? The value 0xFFFF in a row is ignored and the row is checked till the end
? If a row starts with the value 0xFFFF, the complete search is aborted and the default values from C_TXT_
DEF_ENG_COD are used
? If a not existing coding cell is calibrated, the whole row is not valid and the next row is checked
? Unused values of ID_TXT_ENG_COD has to be ?lled with "- ? -"

SYCF, Variant coding
Due to the OBD regulation for each CAL ID a distinct CVN has to be calculated.
CVN calculation has to include some OBD and emission relevant variants, which could be changed by variant
coding.
Thus after variant coding the old CVN will be unvalid. The new CVN will be calculated due to the requirements
like a completely new reprogrammed ECU.
An area with size of 32 Byte will be added to memory areas relevant for the calculation of the CVN.
Following data of variant coding will be additionaly included in the calculation of the CVN:

SYCF, Variant coding diagnosis
68.6.1 ACTION_SYCF_IndicateWrongMsgRcv
If an message arrives, which due to varaint code or calibarted data is not expected to be received, this action
has to be called. The variant code diagnosis will be informed by data from this Action about not expected mes-
sage.
case 1: PRM_IDX = NC_IDX_VAR_DIAG_TCU
(wrong variant coding automatic transmission system):
IF LV_VAR_CAN_TCU = 0
THEN LV_VAR_COD_NOT_PLAUS_TCU = 1
IF C_VARCOD_DIAG_DI Bit 0 = 0
THEN LV_VAR_COD_NOT_PLAUS = 1
ELSE " diagnosis disabled"
ENDIF
ELSE "do nothing"
ENDIF
case 2: PRM_IDX = NC_IDX_VAR_DIAG_TCS
wrong variant coding traction control system:
IF LV_VAR_CAN_TCS= 0
THEN IF C_VARCOD_DIAG_DI Bit 1 = 0
THEN LV_VAR_COD_NOT_PLAUS = 1
ELSE " diagnosis disabled"
ENDIF
ELSE "do nothing"
ENDIF
case 3: PRM_IDX = NC_IDX_VAR_DIAG_ACU
wrong variant coding airbag system:
IF LV_VAR_CAN_ACU= 0
THEN IF C_VARCOD_DIAG_DI Bit 2 = 0
THEN LV_VAR_COD_NOT_PLAUS = 1
ELSE " diagnosis disabled"
ENDIF
ELSE "do nothing"
ENDIF
case 4: PRM_IDX = NC_IDX_VAR_DIAG_CCU
wrong variant coding air conditioning system:
IF LV_VAR_CAN_CCU = 0
THEN IF C_VARCOD_DIAG_DI Bit 3 = 0
THEN LV_VAR_COD_NOT_PLAUS = 1
ELSE " diagnosis disabled"
ENDIF
ELSE "do nothing"
ENDIF
case 5: PRM_IDX = NC_IDX_VAR_DIAG_DCC
wrong variant distance cruise control:
IF LV_DCC_ENA = 0
THEN IF C_VARCOD_DIAG_DI Bit 4 = 0
THEN LV_ERR_RCV_MSG_DCC=1
ELSE LV_ERR_RCV_MSG_DCC = 0
ENDIF

� General Information
Handle activation/deactivation of transport and production mode and correlated error treatment.
The scope of this speci?cation is to handle the activation/deactivation of transport and production mode.
These modes are used to restrict speci?c functionalities (e.g. limit vehicle speed, RPM or torque) during pro-
duction of the car and during the transfer to the ?nal customer.
This speci?cation refers to the customer document "Konzernfunktionslastenheft Produktions- und Transport-
modus f�r abgasrelevante Steuerger�te" version V 1.4.3 (without Hybrid functionality)
The Transport/Production mode functionality consists of two subfunctionalities.
The production mode is activated to restrict speci?c functionality (e.g. speed limitation, limitation of torque,
limitation of RPM) within the car during its production. The request for the activation/deactivation of the
production mode is received through a diagnostic service during the actual driving cycle and evaluated during
the PWL phase. The request is then stored in non volatile memory and the production mode becomes active/
non active during the next driving cycle.
The transport mode is activated to restrict speci?c functionality (e.g. speed limitation, limitation of torque, limita-
tion of RPM) within the car during the transfer to the ?nal customer. The request for the activation/deactivation
of the transport mode has to be received two subsequent times through an intersystem communication mes-
sage during PWL phase. The request is then stored in non volatile memory and the transport mode becomes
active/non active during the next driving cycle.
Furthermore, the evaluation of the intersystem communication message can be activated/deactivated through
a diagnostic service request during a driving cycle.
The error memory treatment depends on the actual state of transport and production mode. If one of the
modes is activated during a driving cycle it becomes active in the next driving cycle. An active mode triggers

Hints:
General
The mode can only be changed during power latch mode, if the actual speed is
below 5 km/h (NC_VS_MAX_TRPT_PROD_PWL = 5).
The detection of transport/production mode is realized through a state machine.
Production mode
The production mode is deactivated automatically after a certain distance has
been travelled (fixed value NC_MAX_DIST_MOD_PROD_DEAC for series ECUs, calibratable
value C_DIST_MAX_MOD_PROD_DEAC for development ECUs; both shown via DIST_MAX_
MOD_PROD_DEAC) and can not be reactivated.
The failure symptom path for the production mode can be enabled/disabled through
calibration (LC_ERR_SYM_MOD_PROD_DEAC = 0/1 (enabled/disabled).
Transport mode
The transport mode is deactivated automatically after a certain distance has
been traveled (fixed value NC_MAX_DIST_MOD_TRPT_DEAC for series ECUs, calibratable
value C_DIST_MAX_MOD_TRPT_DEAC for development ECUs; both shown via DIST_MAX_
MOD_TRPT_DEAC) and can not be reactivated.
An active transport mode or a request can be overwritten by an active production
mode or a request. The behaviour is controlled through calibration
(LC_STATE_PROD_INH_TRPT_DEAC = 0/1 enabled (default)/disabled)
The failure symptom path for the transport mode can be enabled/disabled through
calibration (LC_ERR_SYM_MOD_PROD_DEAC = 0/1 (enabled/disabled).
During the acquisition of the CAN transport mode signal (CASE = 1, the signal
has to be received twice with the same value to be valid) the recurrence of the
function is much higher than the one of the CAN signal. The number of recurrences
within this case is limited to NC_CTR_CYC_TRPT_PROD_MAX_PWL = 300 (300 x 10ms
= 3s).
68.7.1 ACTION_SetPModeState
Action to request an activation or deactivation of the production mode. This action is called by the diagnostic
package upon reception of a service request ($2E).

� General Information
There are different drivetrain requirements of a vehicle in case of normal lifetime at customer and in case
of tests on the vehicle dyno. Due to these differences, the evaluation of the dynamometer mode has been in-
troduced. It signalizes the complete vehicle system, that the vehicle is on the dyno (e.g. due to emission
test) and the system itself can then react in a certain way.
The dynamometer mode deactivates/modi?es certain components to ensure a safe operating on the dyno
and to be able to carry out comparable results of fuel consumption trips.
After the activation/deactivation of the dynamometer mode, this state stays permantely active/deactive, also
in case of a ignition key cycle, as long until the dyno mode is deactivated via tester or the ESP detects a
normal road drive. The information about the active/deactive state of the dynamometer mode needs to be
stored immediately to the non volatile memory, means writing on the ?y. Is this storage ?nished successfully,
a feedback bit LV_DYNO_MOD_ACT_STOR_OK is set. After each reset, the state of the dynamometer mode
needs to be read out of the non volatile memory and used within the system. The variable which indicated
the dynamometer mode is LV_DYNO_MOD_ACT.
The dynamometer mode is activated, if following conditions are ful?lled at the same time:
? via service tool, using service 0x2E, the request for the activation of the dynamometer mode is initiated
and
? there is no or only the DynoMod failure entry in the failure memory (possible to be bypassed with
calibration LC_DYNO_MOD_DIAG_RLV_DI) and
? the FARM interface has permission and
? the ignition key is on and
? the vehicle speed is zero and
? the combustion engine speed is zero and
? the electric motor is off and
? the speed of the electric motor is zero.
? road drive is detected
It is also possible to link only relevant errors to the activation and deactivation condition using FARM.
The dynamometer mode is deactivated, if following conditions are ful?lled at the same time:
? via service tool, using service 0x2E, the request for the deactivation of the dynamometer mode is initi-
ated and
? the ignition key is on and
? the vehicle speed is zero and
? the combustion engine speed is zero and
? the electric motor is off and
? the speed of the electric motor is zero.

SYCF, Dynamometer Mode
The dynamometer mode is also deactivatedimmediately (without the check of the above described deactiva-
tion conditions) in case of ESP is sending the information via CAN that a normal run on the road is detected and
therefore dynamometer mode needs to be deactivated (LV_STATE_ROAD_VEH_DET = 1). For safety reasons,
this deactivation is done only after a certain debouncing of the received signal.
All consumers of the state of the dynamometer mode need to deactivate their reactions immediately (if there
are any) in case of a deactivation of the dynamometer mode.
The error memory treatment depends of the actual state of the dynamometer mode. At activated dynamome-
ter mode, a failure entry into the failure memory is triggered directly and reported to a connected service tool.
If the mode is deactivated, the error symptom of the dynamometer mode needs to be set directly to deactive,
but it?s stored error needs to stay into the failure memory for several warmup cycles until it gets removed
?nally from the failure memory.
Using service 0x22, the current state of the dynamometer mode can be read out by a service tool.
Dependent on the used vehicle communication network, a status bit is provided to other control units to
inform them about the current state of the dynamometer mode.

The image displays variant coding configuration data, likely for an automotive ECU related to emission control. It defines the possible values and their meanings for various parameters.

## Function

The primary function of the data displayed in the image is to define the valid configurations for emission-related variant coding within a vehicle's electronic control unit (ECU).
